node.title: They Said the Tornado Would Hit at 9:30. It Hit at 9:30.
node.description: Scientists have reached success rates of nearly 100 percent in predicting when and where tornadoes will strike. That hasn’t stopped people from being killed in the ferocious winds.

node.title: O.J. Simpson’s Parole Supervision Ends
node.description: The former football star served nine years in prison for robbery before he was granted parole in 2017. His supervision ended two months early because of good behavior.

node.title: Waterboarded Prisoner Has Drowning Nightmares Two Decades Later, Doctor Testifies
node.description: Lawyers called a torture expert in a bid to spare a defendant a nauseating commute from prison to court by having him spend nights at Guantánamo Bay’s court compound.

node.title: Maryland’s Wayward Zebras Have Been Captured After Nearly Four Months
node.description: The two zebras had escaped with another, which was later found dead, from a suburban farm, delighting residents and evading attempts to capture them, the authorities said.

node.title: Romanian Judge Focused on Reform of Country's Judicial System Suspended for TikTok Posts
node.description: Cristi Danilet said the suspension for the posts of himself doing basic tasks at home is "payback" for his years of advocating for judicial reforms in Romania.

node.title: Amid Staff Exits and Toxic Workplace Whispers, Kamala Harris Picks Up $1.2B Win at Border
node.description: Some reportedly felt that by tapping Harris to address the border, Biden was saddling her with an "all-around politically losing assignment."

node.title: Lawsuit Alleges Staff at Vermont Juvenile Detention Center Stripped Kids, Used Restraints
node.description: A lawsuit claimed that children experienced frequent abuse between 2016 and 2020 and were physically, mentally, and/or sexually abused by staff members.

node.title: Californians Trapped by Mudslides in the Canyons as Rainstorms Show No Mercy
node.description: Nearly 7 inches of rain had fallen northwest of Los Angeles by Tuesday.

node.title: After a three-year battle, the WTO has ruled in favour of Australian cane farmers — so what does it mean now?
node.description: Half a world away from Australia's cane fields, a decision has been made that will affect farmers across the country.

node.title: 'We are coming after you': Washington sues the Proud Boys and Oath Keepers over US Capitol attack
node.description: The lawsuit invokes the Ku Klux Klan Act of 1871, which allows people to sue for civil rights violations — a move some hope will expose the financial support structure of the far-right extremist network.

node.title: Homicide investigation into 48yo man's death in Te Awamutu
node.description: Police have launched a homicide investigation over a death at a Te Awamutu property.

node.title: Man exonerated in Malcolm X's murder sues New York state
node.description: Muhammad Aziz is suing the state of New York for at least $20 million.
